chapter.verse:
Now when it was evening, the disciples came to him and said, 


This is a desolate place, and the day is now over; 


send the crowds away to go into the villages and buy food for themselves.

But Jesus said, 



	They need not go away; 


	you give them something to eat.

but the boat by this time was a long way


 from the land,


 beaten by the waves, for the wind was against them.
